CMS Enhancements Inc said it hasintroduced the first add-on mass storage products for the newInternational Business Machines Corp &lt;IBM> IBM PersonalSystem/2 Model 30 personal computers.    CMS said the products are available immediately and includehard disk drives, tape backup subsystems and a hard disk driveon an expansion card.    It added it plans to introduce more products for higher-end models of the IBM personal computers within the next twomonths.    Prices for the new products range from 795 dlrs for a tapebackup subsystem, to 5,695 dlrs for a mass storage subsystem. Reuter&#3;